BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:daily-pipeline-run@predictor-ingest
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260309T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260309T133000
RRULE:FREQ=DAILY
SUMMARY:Run Daily Pipeline (AI + Biosafety + Film)
DESCRIPTION:Run all domain pipelines:\n\n  make daily\n  make daily DOMAIN=biosafety\n  make daily DOMAIN=film\n\nThen review extraction logs for errors.\nCheck data/extractions/ for new output.
CATEGORIES:Pipeline
STATUS:CONFIRMED
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT10M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Pipeline run in 10 minutes
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:weekly-quality-review@predictor-ingest
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260313T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260313T160000
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;BYDAY=FR
SUMMARY:Weekly Quality Review
DESCRIPTION:Review extraction quality metrics for all domains:\n\n  python scripts/collect_metrics_gist.py\n  python scripts/collect_metrics_gist.py --domain biosafety\n  python scripts/collect_metrics_gist.py --domain film\n\nCheck:\n- Evidence fidelity rates (note: Gate A disabled for film — orphan/zero-value/high-conf still enforced)\n- Orphan endpoint counts\n- Entity resolution drift\n- Feed health / 404s\n- Trend scoring sanity
CATEGORIES:Quality
STATUS:CONFIRMED
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT15M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Quality review in 15 minutes
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:backend-b10-backtest@predictor-ingest
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260329T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260330T000000
SUMMARY:Backend B.10 Unblocked (~30 days pipeline data)
DESCRIPTION:Backtest harness (scripts/backtest.py) becomes viable around late March\nwhen >=30 days of pipeline data are available.\n\nSee: docs/research/trend-insights.md Phase B\nSee: docs/project-plan.md Backend Track B.10
CATEGORIES:Backend,Milestone
STATUS:TENTATIVE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:badge-contrast-fix-20260324@predictor-ingest
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T150000
SUMMARY:Fix badge gray-on-gray contrast issues
DESCRIPTION:Badge contrast regression — gray-on-gray still appearing in some situations.\nInvestigate which badge variants are affected.\nDefault .badge: white text on --gray-500 background.\nCheck dark mode token values and entity types falling through to default styling.\nPrevious fix: film domain badge contrast fixes (10 new type rules)\, default badge white-on-gray for dark mode.\n\nReference: branch fix/hot-panel-bounce-and-narrative has the intended changes but conflicts with main — cherry-pick the badge.css\, button.css\, toolbar.css diffs manually rather than merging.
CATEGORIES:UI,Task
STATUS:NEEDS-ACTION
PRIORITY:3
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT10M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Badge contrast fix scheduled
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
